You are currently viewing:
This Employment Contract Transition Option Bonus clause is from the contract involving XERIUM V US LTD | Xerium Technologies, Inc. RealDealDocs contains millions of easily searchable legal documents and clauses from top law firms. Search our Legal Agreements or our Contract Clause Library for free.




Title: AMENDMENT NO. 3 TO EMPLOYMENT AGREEMENT Governing Law: Employment Agreement Amendment North Carolina Date: 12/22/2011 


















50 of the Top 250 law firms use our Products every day










(iv)  - Transition Option Bonus.
		On the date the Transition Incentive Bonus is paid, the Company will grant the Executive an option to purchase 40,000 shares of the Companys common stock at a price equal to the greater of $16.00 per share or the then fair market value of such shares. The option will be fully vested at grant and have a term of five (5) years.		












 


















